org.intellimate.izou.sdk.output

Class OutputPluginArgument<T,X>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.intellimate.izou.sdk.util.AddOnModule
      • org.intellimate.izou.sdk.output.OutputPluginArgument<T,X>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the Argument
    X - the return type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable, Identifiable, OutputPluginModel<T,X>, ContextProvider, Loggable, LoggedExceptionCallback, ThreadPoolUser, ExceptionCallback
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OutputPlugin

    public abstract class OutputPluginArgument<T,X>
extends AddOnModule
implements OutputPluginModel<T,X>, ThreadPoolUser
    The OutputPlugin class gets Event and then starts threads filled with output-extension tasks to create the final output and then render it on its own medium

      • run

        public void run()
        main method for outputPlugin, runs the data-conversion and output-renderer it will instruct the outputManager to let the outputExtensions generate the data. Wait for the time specified in getTimeoutLimit() (standard is 1000 milliseconds) abd the call renderFinalOutput() with the resulting data.
        Specified by:
        run in interface Runnable
